gomodel:SYNGO_1824  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1e,f,g,h; overexpression of IL1RAPL2 in hippocampal neurons promotes excitatory but not inhibitory synapses formation\nLiteral:\n\"Similar to IL1RAPL1, IL1RAPL2 over-expression increased the dendritic spine number without affecting morphology\"\n\nFig. 2; IL1RAPL1 and IL1RAPL2 promote functional excitatory synapse formation.\nLiteral:\n\"IL1RAPL1 and IL1RAPL2 are able to induce synapsin I clustering in contacting axons of co-cultured neurons.\"\n\n7/6/2017 Pim\n- The term \"presynapse assembly\" is allowed over \"synapse assembly\" because of the experiments in non-neuronal cels where expressed IL1RAPL1 is able to induce aggregation of presynaptic marker proteins.\n- Data in this paper does NOT sufficiently claim a role in transsynaptic signaling as show and claimed for the IL1RAPL1 paralog in additional figures.. Experimental description: 7/6/2017 Pim\n- Species of the over-expressed protein is not mentioned in the paper: \"IL1RAPL2 cDNA was first obtained by Kristi Palmer (Amgen)\"\n- Personal communication with the authors: \"The IL1RAPL2 cDNA is from human gene\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1824" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

